<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-009-182 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 503 702</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 20 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fujitsu offers memory card controller evaluation kit. (FujitsuMicroelectronics Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbara E.; McMullen, John F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Fujitsu Microelectronics Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Fujitsu MB86301 (Microcontroller) (Equipment and supplies).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionBoards/CardsMicroprocessors.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Fujitsu Offers Memory Card Controller Evaluation Kit 11/20/91 SAN FRANCISCO,CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1991 NOV 20 (NB)  -- Fujitsu Microelectronics Inc. (FMI)has announced the release of a product that allows customers to evaluate thecompany's MB86301 8- and 16-bit memory card controllers in realistic systemconfigurations.andM;According to the statement released by Larry Gagliani, Fujitsu memory cardproduct marketing manager: &quot;the MB86301 evaluation kit includes all thehardware, software, and documentation designers need to demonstratefeasibility and immediately start prototyping an x86-based system designusing Fujitsu memory card technology.&quot;andM;The evaluation kit contains a full-size PC AT-compatible MB86301 evaluatorboard, a sample Fujitsu flash memory card, PC AT- compatible software,schematics, and Fujitsu's Memory Data Book.andP;  The evaluator board and supportsoftware were jointly developed by FMI and Databook Inc., of Ithaca, NewYork.andP;  The kit is scheduled for availability in January 1992 at a suggestedretail price of $499.andM;The memory card technology is presently utilized by Poqet and Hewlett-Packardin their palmtop computers, by IBM in its radio- based MS-DOS personalcomputer and by NCR in its pen-based personal computer system.andP;  According tothe Fujitsu statement.andP;  both the MB86301 controller IC and MB86301-EVAL-Aevaluator kit conform to the PCMCIA (Personal Computer Memory InternationalAssociation) release 2.0 and the JEIDA (Japan Electronic Industry DevelopmentAssociation) version 4.1 standards for memory cards that is used in thesecomputers.andM;The MB86301 evaluator board, designed for use with any PC AT- compatiblecomputer equipped with ISA (Industry Standard Architecture) bus expansioncard sockets, can read and program flash, EPROM (erasable programmableread-only memory), OTPROM, and EEPROM (electrically EPROM) cards as well asread and write SRAM cards.andP;  Two programmable power supplies are intended tofacilitate the programming of non-volatile memory cards.andP;  A voltage sagdetection circuit is included to demonstrate the circuit design techniquesused to insure data integrity for volatile SRAM memory cards.andP;  Fujitsu alsoprovides a complete set of evaluator board schematics with the kit.andM;(Barbara E. McMullen andamp; John F. McMullen/19911120/Press Contact: CharlieShafton, Fujitsu Microelectronics Inc., 408-922-9825)</TEXT></DOC>